page.title: 14The Manse Wood, Tongue
page.content: 'We don't have many trees in Tongue, but there is a small wood beside the school and we went there one after noon to see how many different kinds of trees there were. We found nine different kinds, birch, hawthorn, ash larch,elm, beech, rowan, alder, white beam. We measured their girths and found the elm and the beech had the biggest girths. There were quite a lot of beech and elmtrees, but there was only one white beam. The big beech trees had been planted years ago, but a lot of the small trees had just seeded themselves.'
